\begin_layout Section*
Methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
My personal predilection is for a rather conventional laboratory experimental
 approach.
 Forward progress is achieved thorough a mixture of theoretical articulations
 and experimental realizations.
 Try to build a system that 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

works
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Collect the data.
 Analyze the data.
 Try to understand 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

what happened
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

lab
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 here is software.
 Software is commonly distinguished into imperative vs.
 functional programming styles.
 Off in a neglected corner is the descriptive or declarative style.
 The declarative style splits computation into two pieces: a description
 of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

what is
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, and a distinct component of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

how it interacts
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 The description of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

what is
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 can be understood as a description of structure, of network relationships,
 of graphical vertexes and edges (or dots and arrows, for category theory/topoi.)
 The 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

how it interacts
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 portion is a dynamical system or driver that mutates structures and relationshi
ps over time.
 The driver is more–or–less structure agnostic; the driver rearranges the
 descriptive/declarative program through combinatoric forces, e.g.
 free energy principles, maximum entropy principles, and/or related non-equilibr
ium thermodynamical principles, including conventional ideas formulated
 
\emph on
a la
\emph default
 Gibbs and Boltzmann, Markov/Bayesian blankets, 
\emph on
etc.

\emph default
 That is, the driver is presumed to accord well with generally–accepted
 conventional concepts.
\end_layout

